          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets used were spectrographically pure copper,",
                "gold, thorium and lanthanum.",
                "The targets were 15 x 5 x *0.5 mm in dimension."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCY"
                ],
                "institute": "4ZZZDUB"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".The Calculated formation thresholds for Na-24",
                "and P-32 in spallation and fission are compared with",
                "the experimental values showing that in Cu,La and Au",
                "these two nuclei are formed mainly by strongly",
                "asymmetric fission. Formation of P-32 from Cu is an",
                "exception, being due to spallation and this process is",
                "also important in the formation of Na-24 from Cu."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Sodium was separated from the exposed copper as",
                "chloride after the precipitation of copper and bismuth",
                "sulphides in weakly acid solution,manganese sulphide in",
                "ammoniac solution,iron hydroxide,potassium",
                "perchlorate and adsorption of cations from 0.3 H-Cl",
                "solution on a chromatographic column packed with KU-2",
                "resin in H+ form. Ammonium salts were removed by",
                "roasting. The sodium chloride was reprecipitated and",
                "dried at 130 degrees. The exposed lanthanum and gold",
                "were analyzed by initially precipitating lanthanum",
                "hydroxide with ammonia and precipitating the gold from",
                " 40% H-Cl solution with SO(2).",
                "In the copper analysis, after precipitation of copper",
                "sulphide, phosphorus was precipitated as ammonium",
                "phosphomolybdate in the presence of 20 mg Be(+2). This",
                "precipitation was repeated twice and the precipitate",
                "dissolved in concentrated ammonia, phosphorus was",
                "separated from this solution using a magnesia mixture",
                " (again repeated twice).The Precipitate was dissolved",
                "in 0.3 N H-Cl and passed through a chromatographic",
                "column packed with KU-2 resin in H+ form, bismuth",
                "phosphate was precipitated from the solution and",
                "dissolved in H-Cl. The bismuth was removed with H(2)S.",
                "Two precipitations of iron cupferronate were carried",
                "out. The phosphorus was precipitated finally as",
                "zirconium phosphate. After reprecipitation it was",
                "roasted at 900C degr. to Zr-P(2)O(7)."
              ]
            }
          ],
